<FONT FACE="Arial,Comic Sans MS,Arial, Helvetica, Geneva" SIZE="+2" color=#cc9900>
<b>Homework</b>
</font><p>

There are three forms of homework.
<ul>
<li>  Most homework will be assigned on WebWork, an online homework system accessible via TSquare.  Online assignments will be due on Thursdays at 11:59 pm.  Note that each week's assignment will consist of problems from 1-2 sections of the text (so they will look like multiple assignments online).
<li>The second form of homework will be written, and will consist of one problem per week, similar to an exam problem, and due on Friday at the start of class.
<li>The third type of homework will consist of two short papers on applications of linear algebra.  The lowest homework grade will be dropped.
</ul>

<p><p>

<FONT FACE="Arial,Comic Sans MS,Arial, Helvetica, Geneva" SIZE="+2" color=#cc9900>
<b>Quizzes</b>
</font><p>

Quizzes will be given during each Friday that has no exam (except the first).  Quizzes will be based on the homework and additionally serve as practice for exams.  The lowest quiz grade will be dropped.

<p><p>

<FONT FACE="Arial,Comic Sans MS,Arial, Helvetica, Geneva" SIZE="+2" color=#cc9900>
<b>Participation</b>
</font><p>

The course will use Piazza, available via TSquare, to perform classroom polling.  Student scores are based solely on participation.  The three lowest participation scores will be dropped.

